article.headline: East Tennessee State defeats Citadel 81-63
article.description: — Ebby Asamoah's 20 points helped East Tennessee State defeat Citadel 81-63 on Wednesday night.
article.story: CHARLESTON, S.C. -- — Ebby Asamoah's 20 points helped East Tennessee State defeat Citadel 81-63 on Wednesday night. Asamoah was 9 of 15 shooting (2 for 6 from 3-point range) for the Buccaneers (15-15, 7-10 Southern Conference). Jaden Seymour scored 14 points while going 6 of 9 from the field. Quimari Peterson had 12 points and shot 6 of 10 from the field. The Bulldogs (11-19, 3-14) were led in scoring by Madison Durr, who finished with 18 points and six assists. AJ Smith added 17 points and six rebounds for Citadel. In addition, Quentin Millora-Brown had 14 points, eight rebounds and two blocks. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
